esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert on Kubernetes Service UpdateLoadBalancerFailed events.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Cloud load balancer update failed — service changes not applied.
//
// Common causes:
// Cloud provider API failures, permission issues, invalid configuration, quota limits.
//
// Action needed:
// Check cloud provider status, verify IAM permissions, review service configuration.
//
// Grouped by cluster, namespace, service name, object kind, and event reason.
// To scope to a specific namespace, add: AND `kubernetes.event.metadata.namespace` == "YOUR_NAMESPACE"
FROM metrics-kubernetes.event-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.event.involved_object.kind` == "Service"
  AND `kubernetes.event.source.component` == "service-controller"
  AND `kubernetes.event.reason` == "UpdateLoadBalancerFailed"
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.event.metadata.namespace`,
     `kubernetes.event.involved_object.name`, `kubernetes.event.involved_object.kind`,
     `kubernetes.event.reason`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
